<TITLE> Policemen caught mugging at ZIA </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Dec 25 (bdnews24.com)--Two policemen were caught on Friday trying to mug a passenger and a money trader at Zia International Airport. The arrestees are Solaiman and Yakub Ali, constables of the fifth battalion of armed police. Deputy commissioner of Uttara Zone of Dhaka Metropolitan Police Nisarul Arif told bdnews24.com police nabbed the two while they were attempting to snatch money. Arif said one passenger sold some Oman currency for Tk ,2000 to an illegal money trader, Taj Mohammad. They first robbed the passenger of Tk 2000 and then tried to snatch away 330 dirham from Mohammed, he added. said As Taj Mohammed cried out, the airport police came to his rescue and nabbed the muggers. On interrogation, they were identified as policemen, he said. The policemen will face departmental action, Arif said adding that Taj Mohammad was also arrested for his involvement in illegal trading. An officer of Adabar Police Station was nabbed during mugging at Paltan early this month and his two associates are still absconding. bdne
